description: The Central African Republic is the first country to receive thousands of doses of a new malaria vaccine recommended by the World Health Organization last October.
title: New malaria vaccine delivered for the first time

description: The World Health Organization hoped to have a treaty ready for ratification at its assembly next week. On Friday, WHO leader Tedros said negotiators couldn't resolve all the sticking points in time.
title: Negotiators for the global pandemic treaty couldn't meet their deadline

description: The Justice Department is suing Ticketmaster and its owner, Live Nation, accusing it of being a monopoly. And, here's why you should think twice before posting a photo of your kid online.
title: DOJ sues Ticketmaster and Live Nation; the dangers of sharing kids' photos online

description: Pollsters and analysts say these could be the most pivotal elections since the country's first democratic vote 30 years ago, in 1994. Here's what's at stake.
title: What to know about South Africa's May 29 elections
